<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894384>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. SEM micrographs of the translucent-yellow short-stalked globose (‘TSG’) trichomes and the minute sessile glands of Drosera quartzicola. A. Adaxial surface of the petiole with multiple TSG trichomes (the ones on the left showing a somewhat moriform shape) and minute sessile glands; B. Lateral view of a single TSG trichome and smaller sessile gland. Micrographs provided by A. Fleischmann." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4894384/files/figure.png" .

